The paper deals with object detection in 360° images, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing, feature extraction, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of distortion and inefficiency in projection techniques, which are related to graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM). The proposed method involves a two-stage object detector, which is a combination of region proposal network and reprojection network, indicating the involvement of robotics (RO) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques.
